From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Umair Ahmed Shah <umairahmedshah@hotmail.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 14:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: broadcom: bcm2712-rpi-5-b: add ramoops reserved
 memory

Add a 1 MiB reserved-memory region and wire a ramoops backend so kernel
panic/oops + console state is persisted across reboot. Forms the BSP-side
half of the pstore-persist capture stack (kernel pstore RAM backend +
systemd-pstore.service archive the records to /data on next boot).

This patch is gated on IOTGW_ENABLE_PSTORE_PERSIST in the Yocto recipe.
Default is enabled for production and dev images; the aggressive lab-only
debug behaviour (sysrq, panic-on-oops, hung-task detector) is a separate
opt-in via IOTGW_ENABLE_CRASH_DEBUG_DEV.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [IoT Gateway BSP crash persistence]
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts
index ad96fb439bd2..d5ecbc95eeee 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts
@@ -105,6 +105,19 @@ / {
 			};
 		};
 	};
+
+	reserved-memory {
+		#address-cells = <2>;
+		#size-cells = <2>;
+		ranges;
+		ramoops@13000000 {
+			compatible = "ramoops";
+			reg = <0x0 0x13000000 0x0 0x00100000>;
+			record-size = <0x00020000>;
+			console-size = <0x00020000>;
+			pmsg-size = <0x00020000>;
+		};
+	};
 };
 
 &rp1_spi0 {
